Giveaway.gstart:
Instantly start a giveaway

Seperators - "|" "," " "

Arguments :

Time - The time until the giveaways ends you can attach [m, h, d, w] to the end to specify minutes, hours, days, or weeks

Winners - The amount of winners the giveaway will have

Requirement - The requirement a user needs to complete or "none". check out [docs.frisky.dev](https://docs.frisky.dev) for more info

Prize - The title of the giveaway embed

Examples:
 +gstart 1m 1w None test
  > time: 1 minute | requirement:
    winners: 1     | prize: test

 +gstart 5m30s 2w Community[role] nitro
  >  time : 5 minutes, 30 seconds | requirement: community role
  >  winners: 2​           ​| prize: nitro

 +gstart 1h8m30s 1w 5[amari];;community[role] test
  > requirement: level 5 amari + community role

Polls.quickpoll:
Quickly setup a poll for the bot to run
arguments >
 - questions and choices : enter the question and the choices for the bot to have

seperators >
 - default seperators you can seperate by "|" or "," if you do not provide a seperator we will seperate by spaces

permissions >
 - requires "ADD_REACTIONS" and "READ_MESSAGE HISTORY"

 (max) > 10 choices
 (min) > 1 question - 2 choices

example >
 `+quickpoll Is Friskytool awesome?, Yes, No, What is Friskytool?, You promised cake`
Polls.poll:
Quick and easy yes/no poll, for multiple answers, use +quickpoll
arguments >
 - question : the question you are asking and the title of the embed

permissions >
 - requires "ADD_REACTIONS" and "READ_MESSAGE_HISTORY"

example >
 `+poll Is Friskytool awesome?`

MessageCounting.messages:
The message count of a user in your server

Arguments:
    - user : Discord Member = The user that you want to view the messages of
     + default = Message Author
MessageCounting.messages adjust:
Increase or decrease the message count of a user

Arguments:
    - Users : list[Discord Member] = The user(s) you want to adjust
    - Count : Number = The amount you want to adjust them by
     + Maximum Value = 10k
     + Minimum Value = -10k
     + User Maximum = 50k
MessageCounting.messages leaderboard:
The message counting leaderboard for your server

Arguments:
    - page : Number = The page of the leaderboard you want to view
     + default = 1
MessageCounting.messages reset: Reset the message count for certain groups
MessageCounting.messages reset user:
Reset the message count for a user or multiple users

Arguments:
    - Users : list[Discord Member] = The users whose message count should be reset
     + multiple = True
MessageCounting.messages reset all: Reset the entire servers' message count
MessageCounting.messages graph: View a bar graph of your top message users
